## **Initiate**
_Each ability costs 1 talent point_

**Abilities:**
- **Expanded Explosion**: Your expertise in crafting explosives has improved the effectiveness of your bombs. When you create or use an explosive device, you increase its radius by 5 feet. For example, a bomb that normally affects a 10-foot radius now affects a 15-foot radius. This increased radius applies to all explosive effects you create, including those from your Improvised Explosives and any similar abilities. This ability’s range increases by 5 feet when you reach 9th Master level (10-foot), and by 10 feet 17th Great-Grandmaster level (20-foot).
- **Caustic Bomb**: As an action, you can create a powerful, improvised explosive from available materials. It deals 3d6 acid damage in a 10-foot radius on a failed Dexterity saving throw, or half as much on a successful save. You can use this ability once per long rest. This ability’s damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th Adept level (4d6), 9th Master level (5d6), 13th Grandmaster level (6d6), and 17th Great-Grandmaster level (7d6).
- **Alchemy Proficiency**: Gain proficiency in Alchemist’s Supplies. You can craft basic alchemical substances, such as acid flasks, potions of healing, and other simple concoctions.
- **Acidic Insight**: You have developed a keen understanding of acidic substances and their effects. You gain advantage on Intelligence (Arcana) and Wisdom (Nature) checks related to acids, alchemical reactions, and chemical processes. This knowledge allows you to identify and analyse unknown substances or toxins with ease.
- **Acidic Precision**: Your expertise with corrosive substances has honed your skill in turning everyday objects into deadly weapons. You gain proficiency with all thrown weapons and improvised thrown weapons.

